<!-- Message body -->
<P>For those that are new to WoW, I thought I would start a general info chain here and we can add to it as we go along.&nbsp; This will mostly be for people that were not in beta and need a few tips.</P>
<P>First off, there are a coupla good websites for info, including</P>
<P><A href="http://wow.warcry.com" target="_blank">http://wow.warcry.com</A></P>
<P><A href="http://wow.allakhazam.com" target="_blank">http://wow.allakhazam.com</A></P>
<P>Try to pick up any lesser tradeskills early, as, to advance in them, you need lower level items initially.&nbsp; For example, if you want to pick up First Aid, you should do early as the bandages required to skill 80 require linen, and once you get to around level 14-15 you are going to start finding more wool and less linen.&nbsp; You can have as many of the lesser skills as you like (cooking, fishing, first aid), but only 2 primary trade skills (i.e. mining, skinning, leatherworking, etc). Basically, you will know when its a primary skill, as a pop will say something like "You only get two tradeskills, are you sure you want to take Underwater Basketweaving as one of them?"</P>
<P>Traveling:&nbsp; In beta WoW was short for World of Walking, heh.&nbsp; Every map has a griffon transport service, but you must first visit them to "Set the route."&nbsp; Every starting area (race starting area) has a capitol as well.&nbsp; In general, to get from one world to another you have to travel between capitols.&nbsp; To travel within that world you can use the griffon service, although you first must explore on foot.&nbsp; Always, always when exploring, find the town on each new map with a griffon master and set the route by clicking on the griffonmaster (will have a green exclamation point).&nbsp; When traveling&nbsp;via griffons&nbsp;it cost some coin, but as you gain levels, it will become miniscule. </P>
<P>Also, between the human world capitol (stormwind) and the dorf town capitol is a tram service (see the map when you are in the capitols).&nbsp; You can travel to dark elf land from the Dorf town of ... Menithal I think, via a boat.&nbsp; These are both free. </P>
<P>You gain experience by uncovering parts of the map.&nbsp; Frequently it will be unclear just how far/deep into a map you gotta go to get the credit exploring, but usually if you look around and see a farm, or building, or quarry, or whatever, head for that, that will likely unlock the map. </P>
<P>Playing:&nbsp; There is NO killstealing in WoW.&nbsp; This is a wonderful feature.&nbsp; Once a player/group has targeted and initiated contact on a mob, its their mob. It doesnt matter if you only do 1 pt damage, and 4 level 60s run in and finish off the mob, its your mob, you get credit for the kill, and the loot/rewards.&nbsp; In beta it was so funny seeing people run up to whack on your mob.... I actually encouraged it, it just helped me kill em faster.&nbsp; </P>
<P>All likely know the con method used here, same as EQ and DAoC, the color of the mob denotes the difficulty of the mob.&nbsp; White being even, yellow/orange/red harder, blue/green easier, gray too low, no exp.&nbsp; Watch for the word Elite.&nbsp; If a mob is named "An Elite Brainsucking Butt Kicking Snotsucker" even though it may be an even con, its MUCH harder, basically WoW's version of a Boss mob.&nbsp; A&nbsp;regular "Brainsucking Butt Kicking Snotsucker" thats even con should be no problem, just&nbsp;hit him with your Platinum Arse Guard Kleenex Box of Brain Protection spell and you should be fine.</P>
<P>Starting at 4 you start getting new spells from your trainer, be sure and visit him every 2 levels to see what new goodies you get.&nbsp; You gotta buy em, so bring cash, they dont accept visa or amex.</P>
<P>I found it helpful to get all the skills on my hunter I could.&nbsp; It cost 10 silver each, so you wont do till later, but you never know when you may get a good sword and if you havent trained it, you cant use it. Now, that being said, dont worry if you dont practice the skill and get it up early.&nbsp; This isnt EQ.&nbsp; When I was level 20, I took bow, and it took all of about 20 minutes to get the bow skill to within 10 pts of my rifle skill.&nbsp; </P>
<P>More to follow, at work, will add to it later.</P><span class="smText"><br /><br />Edited by Aramyr on 24/11/2004 at 6:19pm</span>
